            . I <rs id="t18200412-138-viclabel789" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18200412-138-crimeloc790">Coach and Horses, in Brewer-street, Golden-square</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-138-crimeloc790" type="placeName" value="Coach and Horses, in Brewer-street, Golden-square"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-138-crimeloc790" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-138-off788 t18200412-138-crimeloc790"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-138-victim1297 t18200412-138-viclabel789"></join>. On the <rs id="t18200412-138-cd791" type="crimeDate">3d of March</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-138-off788 t18200412-138-cd791"></join>, about seven o'clock, the prisoner came with a bottle, I served him with half a pint of rum, which I put into the bottle; he gave me a 1 l. note, I asked who it was for? he said,</p>
               <p>"Mr. Shearman, No. 6, Pulteney-street," which I wrote on it, and asked him if he worked there? he said Yes. I knew a Mr. Shorman, lived there, and suspected him, as he did not give the name. I said it was a bad one, he immediately made a snatch at it, but did not get it - he ran away, leaving the note behind and the bottle. I ran after the prisoner, and called out Stop him! he was stopped, and was not out of my sight. I gave him in charge. (Looks at a note) - this is it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-138-person1298">
